      "component": "article",
      "metadata": {
        "source": "github.readme"
      },
      "html": "\n<p><em>egg</em> is the successor to <a href=\"https://github.com/Wiredcraft/eggshell\">egghsell</a> and keeps the same overall goal; providing a SASS/Bourbon boilerplate. It was developed originally for building Web apps at <a href=\"https://wiredcraft.com\">Wiredcraft</a> (things like <a href=\"http://devo.ps\">devo.ps</a>).</p>\n<p><strong>More on the official page: <a href=\"http://wiredcraft.github.io/egg/#about\">http://wiredcraft.github.io/egg/#about</a></strong>.</p>\n<h2>How to use?</h2>\n<p><em>egg</em> is supposed to be a simple starting point for your styles rather than a\ndependency;</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Dependencies</strong>; <code>bower install</code> to add bourbon and normalize (scss version) or edit the <code>egg.scss</code> to change the import path for these dependencies.</li>\n<li><strong>Hack</strong>; you could simply <code>@import egg.scss</code> and override the styles, or start\nmodifying the files. <code>partials/</code> is definitely fair game, <code>modules/</code> too if you\nknow what you&apos;re doing.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>More details at <a href=\"http://wiredcraft.github.io/egg/#how-to/\">http://wiredcraft.github.io/egg/#how-to/</a></strong>.</p>\n<h2>/docs</h2>\n<p>To build the styles for the public page (in <code>docs/</code>):</p>\n<pre><span class=\"hljs-comment\">cd</span> <span class=\"hljs-comment\">docs</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">sass</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-comment\">sourcemap=none</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-comment\">style</span> <span class=\"hljs-comment\">compressed</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-literal\">-</span><span class=\"hljs-comment\">watch</span> <span class=\"hljs-comment\">styles</span><span class=\"hljs-string\">.</span><span class=\"hljs-comment\">scss:styles</span><span class=\"hljs-string\">.</span><span class=\"hljs-comment\">css</span></pre><p>Obviously, drop the <code>--watch</code> option if you&apos;re not actively working on it.</p>\n"
